basics.name: Youssef Hussein
basics.label: Graduate Research Assistant and Fellow
basics.summary: A graduate research assistant at University of Minnesota researching big data systems with a focus on big spatial data.

work.name: University of Minnesota - Twin Cities
work.summary: Conducting research in the area of Big Data Management and Systems Architecture focusing on SpatioTemporal Data. Supervised by Prof. Mohamed Mokbel
currentProjects: iHARP data infrastructure for polar scientists: Developed and presented a web portal (iharpv.cs.umn.edu) for interactively querying and visualizing raster data.
KAFYTraj An Extensible System For Trajectory Operations Using LLMs: Building a suitcase of LLMs analogous to HuggingFace to build and extend multiple trajectory operations.
highlights: Packaging the system in an extensible easy-to-use python library pypi.org/project/KAFYTraj/

awards.title: Nobel Prize in Physics
awards.summary: The Nobel Prizes are five separate prizes that, according to Alfred Nobel's will of 1895, are awarded to 'those who, during the preceding year, have conferred the greatest benefit to humankind.'
